05101nam a22008535i 9781501509858DE-B159720210526051534.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210526t20202020gw     fo  d z      eng d  a2020936597  a97815015098587 a10.1515/97815015098582doi  a(DE-B1597)494674  a(OCoLC)1191864125  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 7aLAN0090002bisacsh1 aGöbbel, Edward, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aExtraposition from NP in English :bExplorations at the Syntax-Phonology Interface /cEdward Göbbel. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter Mouton, c[2020] 4c©2020  a1 online resource (X, 368 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aInterface Explorations [IE] ;v3600tFrontmatter -- tPreface -- tContents -- t1 Introduction -- t2 Syntactic issues -- t3 The syntax-phonology correspondence -- t4 Phonological solutions -- t5 Defocused and light PPs -- t6 Concluding remarks -- tA List of constraints -- tBibliography -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe impact of phonology on word order phenomena has become a central research agenda ever since the Minimalist Program emphasised the role of interface conditions on syntactic operations. This book is a detailed study of extraposition from NP, which has traditionally been the domain of syntactic investigation and information-structural studies. After an examination of syntactic accounts of PP and relative clause extraposition, which are largely found inadequate, it explores the possibility of phonological solutions by comparing the prosodic structure of canonical and extraposed word orders. Particular attention is payed to the informational status of extraposed constituents and the focus structure of the sentence. The book shows that extraposition optimises the prosodic structure of sentences and in some cases their rhythmic structure, while focus structure only plays a role in extraposition of defocused constituents. The book further argues that extraposition occurs at PF, while certain binding-theoretical consequences of extraposition can be resolved by LF movement. With its focus on the interface between syntax and phonology, the book will appeal to researchers working on either domain.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aExtraposition.  aInformation Structure.  aPhase Theory.  aProsodic Structure.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package 2020z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2020z978311069628808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter English eBooks 2020 - UCz978311065906108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton Frontlist 2020z978311074316608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2020 Englishz978311070476108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2020z9783110704563oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97815015098340 cprintz978150151671940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150150985840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501509858423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501509858.jpg  a978-3-11-065906-1  De Gruyter English eBooks 2020 - UCb2020  a978-3-11-069627-1  DG Ebook Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-069628-8  DG Ebook Package English 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070476-1  EBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-074316-6  D